# Agent Tokens for the AI Hero Content CMS

Matt asked (Slack #cc-matt-p, 2026-07-16) for a flow where he can mint a read-only auth token for the AI Hero CMS for his agents — "read only but privileged (private/unpublished)? — Yep, exactly." Joel's framing: extend the recent OpenAPI/agent-discovery work into a real agent auth system, not a one-off hack.

## Finish line

All of the following hold in production, asserted live (no "verification remaining" prose):

1. An admin mints an agent token over the API (no UI — agentic only).
2. A request bearing that token reads at least one **unpublished** post through the content API.
3. A write attempt with the same token returns 403.
4. Both events appear in Axiom as structured auth log lines (token kind, publicId prefix, scope, outcome).
5. Matt has the how-to in the Slack thread and confirms his agent works against it.

Maintained by: the coverage matrix test suite in CI (route × method × token kind × expected status) — a behavior change that breaks the contract fails the build; `lastUsedAt` + Axiom give the audit trail.

## Vocabulary

- **agent token** — an `aih_pat_*` personal access token minted by an admin for non-human callers; the existing dormant lib `apps/ai-hero/src/lib/personal-access-tokens.ts`.
- **scope-derived ability** — the CASL ability built from the token's scopes alone, never from the owning user's roles; the token row is the full statement of its blast radius.
- **privileged read** — read access that includes drafts, unpublished, and private content; what `content:read` grants.
- **coverage matrix** — the route × method × token-kind × expected-status table, checked in and run in CI; it is the contract for this scope and every future scope.
- **auth seam** — `getUserAbilityForRequest` as the single place any bearer credential becomes `(user, ability, authMethod)`; today device-token-only.

## Notes

- Owning repo/app: `badass-courses/ai-hero`, `apps/ai-hero`. Ultracite standards apply (`bun x ultracite fix` before commit).
- **Execution authorized** (Joel, 2026-07-17): task steps build and ship the system; customer-visible surface = API only.
- Standing calls (Joel, 2026-07-17, at charter):
  - API-only, no UI — "it's agentic only so it doesn't need ui."
  - Ability derives from scope, not owner roles; non-destructive full content/CMS read.
  - Optional `expiresAt` at mint, default none; revocation is the kill switch; stamp `lastUsedAt` on verify.
  - Four systemic improvements ride along: (1) one auth seam, (2) typed scope registry → CASL rules, (3) structured auth observability, (4) OpenAPI `securitySchemes` + agent-discovery documents auth.
  - Minting gated on admin ability, mint-for-self, token attributed to the minting user.
  - (2026-07-17, at matrix approval) Handoff is a paste-able **agent prompt**, not human docs: Matt points his agent at a URL with his admin PAT and it self-onboards from the discovery doc + OpenAPI spec. Add agent instructions wherever needed.
  - (2026-07-17, at matrix approval) The three pre-existing anonymous holes (resources single-read, uploads/signed-url, search visibility) close inside the seam step; #cc-matt-p heads-up at ship for the behavior change.
  - (2026-07-17) No drizzle migration for the PAT table — this app syncs schema via `db:push`; the migrations dir is hand-written one-offs. Prod provisioning is agent-executable: pscale service token creates AND approves deploy requests into the aihero DB; Vercel CLI writes env vars. Secret must exist in Vercel before the required-env change deploys.
- Joel's standing rules that bind here: observability is a launch gate; live remainders must block; Matt heads-up on surface changes (Matt is the requester — delivery is the reply in his thread).
- No prototype step chartered: the design settled at charter; the first touchable artifact is the coverage matrix draft, which the approval grilling reacts to.
- Slack context: https://eggheadio.slack.com/archives/C0211NSK3TP/p1784281556387689

## Decision ledger

- [Inventory the Content API Surface and Draft the Coverage Matrix](./inventory-content-api-surface.svx) — 50 route-method rows inventoried; privileged content reads include posts, lessons, safe resources/search, product structure, and survey definitions, while Mux playback, uploads/signed URLs, memory, survey-response PII, and commerce analytics stay out.
- [Ship Admin-Gated Mint, List, and Revoke Endpoints](./ship-token-mint-endpoints.svx) — admin-only mint-for-self, safe own-token listing, idempotent owned-token revocation, required server secret wiring, structured denial/lifecycle logs, and focused route tests shipped; deployed env secret plus `db:push`/table confirmation remain operator gates before live verification.
- [Provision the Production PAT Prerequisites](./provision-prod-pat-prerequisites.svx) — `PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET` now exists in Vercel production, preview, and development; production `ai-hero.main` already contained `AI_PersonalAccessToken`, so no deploy request was needed.
- [Approve the Coverage Matrix Edges](./approve-coverage-matrix.svx) — all edges locked as drafted; the three anonymous holes close inside the seam step (with Matt heads-up); handoff becomes a paste-able agent prompt against a self-sufficient discovery surface.
- [Wire PAT Verification into the Auth Seam with Scope-Derived Ability](./wire-pat-auth-seam.svx) — `content:read` PATs now verify at the request seam, receive scope-only privileged-read CASL rules, expose safe draft/private reads, deny every matrix write/capability edge with 403, close the three anonymous holes, and pass the 50-row/150-case behavioral matrix.
- [Teach OpenAPI and Agent Discovery the Bearer Scheme](./document-auth-in-openapi.svx) — `/api`, `/api/openapi.json`, and `/llms.txt` now self-teach bearer presentation, admin mint/list/revoke, the scope table, privileged-read edges and exclusions, token lifecycle, and 401/403 recovery; auth error bodies point back to discovery without changing status behavior.

## Latent

- Upstream the mint/verify/ability pattern to course-builder so every product gets agent tokens (PAT table already lives in the shared coursebuilder schema).
- Migrate admin device tokens (90-day TTL, raw-token-in-db) onto the PAT system.
- Future scopes: `content:write`, `analytics:read` enforcement on the analytics routes, `analytics:chat`.
- OAuth client-credentials flow for agents if token sharing across Matt's fleet gets awkward.
- Token-management UI if the audience ever grows past admins.
- Sanitized transcript/content projection for video resources so agents can read transcript text without playable Mux identifiers (matrix excludes `/api/[videoResourceId]` GET as-is).
- Dedicated media/storage scope if agents ever need signed URLs; memory-specific scope for the support-memory routes.
- Observer bus source for `auth.personal-access-token.verify` Axiom events (denial-spike alerting on Matt's agents) — seam listed in `dark-wizard:.brain/resources/matt-course-video-manager.svx` (rig follows via dispatch-rules, live for #cc-matt-p Slack; Axiom/GitHub/Dropbox sources not built yet).

## Out of scope

- Any UI for minting/managing tokens — Joel, 2026-07-17: agentic only.
- Upstreaming to course-builder now — proven-on-AI-Hero first (see Latent).
